    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-02-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-02-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="242"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d242">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Pruyn</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 88.] </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-02-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">February</hi> 9, 1865.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>; Your despatches No. 64, of October 28, No. 65, of
                    October 29, No. 66, of November 29, No, 67, of November 29, and your private
                    note of the same date, have been received, and your proceedings as related
                    therein are approved.</p>
                <p>Your No. 65 is accompanied by a copy of a convention concluded on the 22d of
                    October last between the treaty powers and the Japanese government. So soon as
                    the original of this instrument shall have been received it will be submitted to
                    the Senate for its consideration with a view to its ratification.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD. </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert H. Pruyn</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,
                            &amp;c., Kanagawa.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
